Title: portal

But, like all the best microgenres, it probably only existed for the duration of this album and a few weeks either side, and Daine has probably sloughed off half a dozen more genre terms since then.

Title: Dirty Old Town

It's interesting the way that traditional culture influenced pop and how the culture bends and reacts around it. Anyway, this hyper specific sub genre is just traditionally folk influenced rock.

Title: You're Gonna Hate What You've Done
Comment:

It's music for long winters and existential dread in a Flint basement.

Letâ€™s call it Rustbelt dreamo.

With many similarities and Rasputina coming earlier, some people say the Dresden Dolls ripped them off.

Title: Before the Earth Was Round
Album: Of the Blue Colour of the Sky
Comment:
Just want to preface that this isnâ€™t a flat earther song.

This song and the whole album itâ€™s on is based on a passage of an obscure 1876 book by A. J. Pleasonton called The Influence of the Blue Ray of the Sunlight and of the Blue Colour of the Sky which was an early precursor to the pseudoscientific practice of color therapy. 

From the wiki:

â€˜The image on the album cover was constructed with a list of twenty-five themes (for example "Unfounded or Wildly Broad Claims", "Wonderment", and "Light/Optics/Color"), each representing a specific color, assigned to each sentence in both the passage and the lyrics. If more than one theme is assigned to the same sentence, the colors are combined with additive mixing. With each sentence being represented by a colored line, the lines are arranged radially giving the impression of beams of multicolored light emanating from the center.â€™

If there are other songs about this, Iâ€™m dying to know.
